{"format": "tiptap/v1", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Restate"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Restate", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " is an open-source durable execution server that sits in front of your existing HTTP services. Unlike Temporal (which requires a separate cluster and database) or Inngest (managed SaaS), Restate ships as a "}, {"type": "text", "text": "single self-contained binary", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " with embedded storage (RocksDB) \u2014 you can run it in minutes on a single machine or alongside your containers without provisioning external databases."}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Restate architecture: callers \u2192 Restate Server (journal + virtual objects) \u2192 your HTTP services"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Differentiators from Temporal and Inngest"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Single binary:", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " Restate ships as one binary with embedded RocksDB storage. No Postgres, no Zookeeper, no separate cluster to manage."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Plain HTTP:", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " your service is a normal HTTP server (FastAPI, Flask, Lambda). Restate calls it, journals the response, and retries if needed \u2014 no SDK threading model, no worker polling loop."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Virtual Objects:", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " a first-class keyed-state primitive. Objects have persistent K/V state and a single-writer queue per object ID \u2014 safe from concurrent mutations without locks."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Idempotency built-in:", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " pass an "}, {"type": "text", "text": "Idempotency-Key", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " header on any HTTP call; Restate deduplicates it automatically, returning the previously stored response without re-executing the handler."}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Installation"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "bash"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Install the Restate Python SDK\npip install restate_sdk\n\n# Download and run the Restate Server binary (single binary, no external DB)\n# macOS / Linux:\ncurl -LsSf https://restate.dev/install.sh | sh\nrestate-server\n\n# Or via Docker:\ndocker run --rm -p 8080:8080 -p 9070:9070 docker.restatedev/restate\n\n# Restate Admin UI / CLI\nnpm install -g @restatedev/restate\nrestate --help\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Defining a Durable Service"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Decorate handler functions with "}, {"type": "text", "text": "@service.handler()", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ". Use "}, {"type": "text", "text": "ctx.run()", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " to create durable steps \u2014 exactly like "}, {"type": "text", "text": "step.run()", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " in Inngest or "}, {"type": "text", "text": "workflow.execute_activity()", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " in Temporal."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import restate\nimport anthropic\n\n# \u2500\u2500 Define a service \u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\nresearch_service = restate.Service(\"ResearchService\")\n\n@research_service.handler()\nasync def generate_research(ctx: restate.Context, topic: str) -> str:\n    # ctx.run() is a durable step:\n    # - On the first call: executes the lambda and persists the result\n    # - On retry (crash / redeploy): replays the persisted result without calling the LLM again\n    outline = await ctx.run(\n        \"generate-outline\",\n        lambda: _call_llm(f\"Create a 5-section outline for: {topic}\"),\n    )\n\n    sections = []\n    for i, title in enumerate(outline.split(\"\\n\")[:5]):\n        content = await ctx.run(\n            f\"section-{i}\",\n            lambda t=title, idx=i: _call_llm(f\"Write section {idx+1}: {t}\"),\n        )\n        sections.append(content)\n\n    return \"\\n\\n\".join(sections)\n\n\ndef _call_llm(prompt: str) -> str:\n    client = anthropic.Anthropic()\n    return client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-sonnet-5\",\n        max_tokens=400,\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt}],\n    ).content[0].text\n"}]}, {"type": "blockquote", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The name passed to "}, {"type": "text", "text": "ctx.run()", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " (e.g., "}, {"type": "text", "text": "\"generate-outline\"", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ") is the step's journal key. If the handler retries after a crash, Restate replays the stored result for that key instead of calling the lambda again. Keep names stable \u2014 changing them invalidates the checkpoint."}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Serving with FastAPI"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from fastapi import FastAPI\nimport restate\n\n# Expose the service via FastAPI\napp = FastAPI()\napp.include_router(restate.fastapi_router([research_service, agent_service]))\n\n# Run: uvicorn main:app --port 9080\n\n# Register with Restate Server (one-time, or after adding new services):\n# restate deployments register http://localhost:9080/restate/v1\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Calling a Service"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Any HTTP client can invoke a Restate-registered service by calling the Restate Server's ingress endpoint. The URL structure is "}, {"type": "text", "text": "/ServiceName/handler_name", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import httpx, asyncio\n\nasync def trigger_research(topic: str) -> str:\n    # Call the ResearchService handler directly via HTTP\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        # Idempotency key: Restate deduplicates requests with the same key\n        resp = await client.post(\n            \"http://localhost:8080/ResearchService/generate_research\",\n            json=topic,\n            headers={\"Idempotency-Key\": f\"research-{topic.lower().replace(' ', '-')}\"},\n        )\n        return resp.json()\n\nasyncio.run(trigger_research(\"Distributed systems for beginners\"))\n"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Idempotency-Key header:", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " Restate stores the response under this key. A duplicate request within the deduplication window (default: 24 hours) returns the stored response \u2014 no handler re-execution."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Async invocation:", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " append "}, {"type": "text", "text": "/send", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " to the URL ("}, {"type": "text", "text": "/ResearchService/generate_research/send", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ") to enqueue the call without waiting for the result. Restate executes it durably in the background."}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Virtual Objects \u2014 Keyed Stateful Handlers"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Virtual Objects are services where each method call is scoped to an "}, {"type": "text", "text": "object ID", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " (a string key). All calls to the same object ID are queued \u2014 only one handler runs at a time per key, eliminating concurrent state mutation without explicit locking."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import restate\n\n# Virtual Object \u2014 keyed state safe from concurrent mutations\nagent_session = restate.VirtualObject(\"AgentSession\")\n\n@agent_session.handler()\nasync def add_message(ctx: restate.ObjectContext, message: str) -> None:\n    # ctx.get / ctx.set \u2014 persistent key-value store keyed to the object ID\n    history: list = await ctx.get(\"history\") or []\n    history.append({\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": message})\n    await ctx.set(\"history\", history)\n\n\n@agent_session.handler()\nasync def get_reply(ctx: restate.ObjectContext, _: None) -> str:\n    history: list = await ctx.get(\"history\") or []\n\n    reply = await ctx.run(\n        \"llm-reply\",\n        lambda: _call_llm_with_history(history),\n    )\n\n    history.append({\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": reply})\n    await ctx.set(\"history\", history)\n    return reply\n\n\ndef _call_llm_with_history(history: list) -> str:\n    import anthropic\n    client = anthropic.Anthropic()\n    return client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-sonnet-5\",\n        max_tokens=300,\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"You are a helpful assistant.\"}] + history,\n    ).content[0].text\n\n# Usage: POST /AgentSession/session-42/add_message  {\"message\": \"Hello\"}\n#        POST /AgentSession/session-42/get_reply     {}\n# Restate queues concurrent calls to the same object ID \u2014 no race conditions.\n"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "ctx.get() / ctx.set():", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " read and write persistent K/V state scoped to the object ID. State survives crashes and server restarts \u2014 it is stored in Restate's RocksDB journal."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Single-writer guarantee:", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " concurrent calls to the same object ID (e.g., "}, {"type": "text", "text": "session-42", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ") are queued. This makes Virtual Objects ideal for conversation history, user session state, and inventory management \u2014 any use case that requires atomic read-modify-write."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "URL structure:", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " "}, {"type": "text", "text": "/VirtualObjectName/object_id/handler_name", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": ". The "}, {"type": "text", "text": "object_id", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " segment is the key."}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Workflows (Long-Running with Signals)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Restate's "}, {"type": "text", "text": "Workflow", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " type is similar to Temporal Workflows: a "}, {"type": "text", "text": "main()", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " handler with exactly-once execution, plus shared handlers that can read/write state or send signals at any point."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import restate\nfrom datetime import timedelta\n\n# Workflow \u2014 long-running, at-most-once execution with signals\ndocument_workflow = restate.Workflow(\"DocumentWorkflow\")\n\n@document_workflow.main()\nasync def run(ctx: restate.WorkflowContext, doc_id: str) -> dict:\n    # Step 1: summarise\n    summary = await ctx.run(\n        \"summarise\",\n        lambda: summarise_document(doc_id),\n    )\n    # Store for query access\n    await ctx.set(\"summary\", summary)\n    await ctx.set(\"status\", \"awaiting-approval\")\n\n    # Step 2: wait for human approval signal (up to 7 days)\n    approved = await ctx.promise(\"approval\").value()  # blocks until signal arrives\n\n    if not approved:\n        await ctx.set(\"status\", \"rejected\")\n        return {\"status\": \"rejected\", \"doc_id\": doc_id}\n\n    # Step 3: publish\n    await ctx.run(\"publish\", lambda: publish_document(doc_id, summary))\n    await ctx.set(\"status\", \"published\")\n    return {\"status\": \"published\", \"doc_id\": doc_id}\n\n\n@document_workflow.handler()\nasync def approve(ctx: restate.WorkflowSharedContext, _: None) -> None:\n    await ctx.promise(\"approval\").resolve(True)\n\n\n@document_workflow.handler()\nasync def reject(ctx: restate.WorkflowSharedContext, _: None) -> None:\n    await ctx.promise(\"approval\").resolve(False)\n\n\n@document_workflow.handler()\nasync def get_status(ctx: restate.WorkflowSharedContext, _: None) -> str:\n    return await ctx.get(\"status\") or \"unknown\"\n"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Promise:", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " the Restate equivalent of Temporal's Signal. "}, {"type": "text", "text": "ctx.promise('name').value()", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " suspends the workflow; a shared handler calls "}, {"type": "text", "text": "ctx.promise('name').resolve(value)", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " to wake it."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Shared handlers:", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " decorated with "}, {"type": "text", "text": "@workflow.handler()", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " (not "}, {"type": "text", "text": "@workflow.main()", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": "). They can run concurrently with the "}, {"type": "text", "text": "main()", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " handler \u2014 useful for approval, status queries, and partial updates."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "At-most-once:", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " a workflow with a given ID can only be started once. Restate deduplicates subsequent start calls, returning the existing workflow's result handle."}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Durable Sleep"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use "}, {"type": "text", "text": "ctx.sleep(timedelta(...))", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " for durable pauses. The handler suspends, the process can be restarted or redeployed, and Restate resumes the handler when the timer fires."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import restate\n\npipeline = restate.Service(\"OnboardingPipeline\")\n\n@pipeline.handler()\nasync def run(ctx: restate.Context, user_id: str) -> None:\n    # Send welcome email \u2014 durable, retried on failure\n    await ctx.run(\"send-welcome\", lambda: send_welcome_email(user_id))\n\n    # Sleep 3 days \u2014 no process held open, survives server restarts\n    await ctx.sleep(timedelta(days=3))\n\n    # Check if user has completed onboarding\n    completed = await ctx.run(\n        \"check-onboarding\",\n        lambda: check_onboarding_complete(user_id),\n    )\n\n    if not completed:\n        await ctx.run(\"send-reminder\", lambda: send_reminder_email(user_id))\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Restate vs Temporal vs Inngest"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Aspect"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Restate"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Temporal"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Inngest"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Infrastructure"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Single binary (RocksDB embedded)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cluster + external DB"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Managed SaaS"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Deploy complexity"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Very low (one binary / Docker)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "High (server + DB + workers)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Zero (hosted)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Serverless"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Via Lambda handler"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Limited (persistent worker needed)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Native"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Keyed state"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Virtual Objects (built-in)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Manual via activity + DB"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "No (use external KV)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Signals / events"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Promise API"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Signal + Query API"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "step.wait_for_event()"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Language support"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "TypeScript (primary), Python, Java, Kotlin, Go"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Python, Java, Go, TypeScript, .NET"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "TypeScript, Python, Go"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Idempotency"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Built-in (Idempotency-Key header)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Workflow ID deduplication"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Step memoization"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "License"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "MIT"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "MIT (server), paid Cloud"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Paid SaaS (free tier)"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common Pitfalls"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Non-determinism in handlers:", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " like Temporal, Restate replays handler code to resume after a crash. Any direct LLM call or HTTP request outside "}, {"type": "text", "text": "ctx.run()", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " will be re-executed on replay. All side effects must go inside "}, {"type": "text", "text": "ctx.run()", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Lambda capture bugs:", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " in Python loops, "}, {"type": "text", "text": "lambda: fn(i)", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " captures "}, {"type": "text", "text": "i", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " by reference. Use "}, {"type": "text", "text": "lambda idx=i: fn(idx)", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " to capture the loop variable's current value."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Large ctx.run() payloads:", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " Restate journals the return value of every "}, {"type": "text", "text": "ctx.run()", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " call. Large LLM responses (10+ KB) accumulate quickly if you have many steps. Return only what downstream steps actually need; store large artifacts in S3."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Service registration:", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " after adding a new handler or service, run "}, {"type": "text", "text": "restate deployments register <url>", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " again. Restate introspects your service to discover new handlers \u2014 it will not pick them up automatically."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Virtual Object deadlock:", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " if a Virtual Object handler calls another handler on the same object ID synchronously, it waits in the queue behind itself \u2014 a deadlock. Use "}, {"type": "text", "text": "/send", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " (async one-way call) or restructure to avoid self-calls."}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Summary"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Restate", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " is a single-binary durable execution server with embedded storage \u2014 the lowest operational overhead of any self-hosted durable execution option."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Wrap all side effects in "}, {"type": "text", "text": "ctx.run()", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": "; use "}, {"type": "text", "text": "ctx.sleep()", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " for durable timers and "}, {"type": "text", "text": "ctx.promise()", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " for signals. Plain HTTP handlers get full durability with minimal SDK ceremony."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Virtual Objects", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " provide keyed persistent state with single-writer safety \u2014 no external database or lock manager needed for stateful agents and session management."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The "}, {"type": "text", "text": "Idempotency-Key", "marks": [{"type": "code"}]}, {"type": "text", "text": " header deduplicates any HTTP call automatically, making it easy to build safe retry logic in client code without modifying the server handler."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Choose Restate when you need Temporal-level durability with minimal infrastructure: no external database, no worker cluster, no ops team. Choose Inngest for zero-infra managed SaaS; choose Temporal for polyglot teams needing the widest SDK ecosystem."}]}]}]}]}}